            Steph Copeland
          
          
            
              I am a graduate student in the Ecology, Evolution, and Marine Biology Department (Young Lab) at the University of California Santa Barbara. I am currently interested in understanding anthropogenic impacts to landscapes and the subsequent responses of vectors and vector-borne diseases to these disturbances. I am originally from Wilmington, Delaware. In my spare time I enjoy surfing, cycling, and walking my dog, Hugo.
